Description: CyberHeart developed the first non-invasive robotic ablation treatment for cardiac arrhythmias.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: CyberHeart Incorporated is developing the first non-invasive robotic ablation treatment for cardiac arrhythmias, such as atrial fibrillation or ventricular tachycardia. The CyberHeart system is designed to address these conditions by dynamically detecting, tracking and compensating for movement of the heart and patient, to ensure accuracy in the delivery of radiation. CyberHeart is creating proprietary cardiac technology utilizing the most accurate robotic radiosurgical system commercially available worldwide, the CyberKnifeÂ® Robotic Radiosurgery System. With an exclusive intellectual property license agreement, CyberHeart will leverage the existing experience and knowledge base to develop this innovative electrophysiology application for the heart. The CyberHeart System is being developed specifically for use by radiation oncologists, medical physicists, electrophysiologists, and cardiac surgeons, to non-invasively treat cardiac arrhythmias. CyberHeart is an early stage, venture capital-backed medical device company founded by Dr. Thomas Fogarty and Roderick Young. The company began operations in 2006 and has been conducting pre-clinical studies that validate the feasibility of the technology. CyberHeart secured $9 million in Series A financing in November 2007.

Description: Mobile App / Platform
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Local App is the best product for people who seek a unique trip, wish to create great memories, & have a personalized experience with a verified Local that you can genuinely trust. A Local is someone from that city who will provide concierge-like services. Each Local can specialize in an aspect of the city and may already have or can create a large network in that area, for example: Culinary, landmarks/history, fitness/health, parties, & others; the user can then choose the type of Local they want.  When starting the app for the first time, a registration screen with two options (Local | Traveler) will appear. If an individual chooses to be a Local, we will run a background check on them, providing an increased level of security and peace of mind to users seeking exotic experiences. After each booking, the Local would receive a 0-5 star rating. The idea is that better Locals get more opportunities and bookings. All users (Travelers and Locals) can post images/videos/reels of the experience and attract exponentially more individuals. Our app gives communities a chance at gentrification: otherwise, unknown regions can attract global attention through our feed features and international marketing. We are currently initiating data collection trials in small municipalities in the north of Brazil to prove this point. Further on, with more tourists visiting smaller communities, the region's economy also gets positively affected, improving the quality of life of thousands and potentially millions.  We solve not one but various problems present in the Tourism and Concierge industries. With our app, it is no longer dangerous, pricey, disconnected, and time-consuming to properly explore a city the way you would like to. It can now be done with a simple click. And along with solving these impediments, we also give people independence, quality, and a chance to be seen.  Local is by the people, for the people.

Description: Amber Biology is a digital biology consulting firm working at the intersection of science and computation.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Amber Biology is a digital biology consulting firm working at the intersection of science & computation. With decades of experience working in academic and commercial environments ranging from universities and medical schools to small venture capital-funded startups and global pharmaceutical companies, we founded Amber Biology to meet the unique demands of life science and other research organizations seeking to bring the power of scientific computing to their own R&D programs. Offering a simple and customer-centric fee-for-service model, Amber Biology’s consultants have successfully applied their specialist skills in algorithm design, data analysis, simulation, and software development, to a wide range of life science research areas including the engineering of therapeutic proteins and nucleic acids, disease diagnosis algorithms, population genetics, exobiology and exoplanet detection, and laboratory robot design. Our clients include major research universities on both U.S. coasts, and commercial life science companies both in the U.S. and in Europe. We are also a contractor on the NASA Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) mission, due to be launched from Cape Canaveral in early 2018. Amber Biology is based in Cambridge, Massachusetts.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Professional Services, Science and Engineering

Description: Race Yourself develops augmented reality (AR) games such as an exercise games platform that uses Google Glass technology.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Exercise is changing.  At the cutting edge of fitness meets entertainment, Race Yourself, is the world's first fitness games company leveraging wearable technology, and augmented reality. We are building a unified digital fitness platform across mobile, web, and wearables (head mounted displays like Glass, Smart Watches etc). Our games and challenges motivate ‘Racers' to achieve their personal best (PB) by allowing them to live-race a three dimensional avatar of themselves (previous run/cycle), their friends, celebrities, or even flesh eating zombies pursuing at their target pace. On foot, bike (in future skis or snow board), whether you're outdoors or in the gym, a serious aspiring athlete training for a big event,  or a casual fitness enthusiast; Race Yourself provides you real-time on-screen technique feedback and encouragement during your exercise and sporting endeavors.  Our vision is to bring the adrenaline-addictiveness of gaming to exercise, to do what Wii Sports did for the Wii but for Glass. With an in-app purchase model harnessing game economy mechanics similar to Clash of Clans, we are creating something healthy that people will want to be hooked on. The experience is best shown in our 1 min concept video, which has had over 185,000 views this last month. http://youtu.be/39W6CMpdGsM

Description: Professional organization promoting the research and clinical use of oral appliance therapy for the treatment of sleep apnea and snoring.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Established in 1991, the American Academy of Dental Sleep Medicine is the only non-profit national professional society dedicated exclusively to the practice of dental sleep medicine. The AADSM is the leading national organization for dentists who use oral appliance therapy to manage sleep-disordered breathing, which includes snoring and obstructive sleep apnea. If left untreated, OSA is a potentially life threatening condition that can increase the risk for serious health problems such as high blood pressure, congestive heart failure, stroke, diabetes and depression. CPAP, or continuous positive airway pressure, is the recommended treatment for sleep apnea. However, up to half of sleep apnea patients don’t comply with CPAP therapy or can’t tolerate it. Oral appliance therapy is an effective treatment option for people who are living with snoring and OSA.

Full Description: Shipzi - The fast, free, and easy way to ship. Shipzi is a fully integrated, cloud-based shipping solution for ecommerce, SMB, and home-based businesses. The solution is free to the customer and boasts a powerful recurring transactional revenue model. Shipzi is the first truly cloud based shipping solution to hit the market.  When you analyze eCommerce platforms they provide everything a small business needs to sell their products online except for a shipping solution.  Shipzi benefits the eCommerce platform by being the fully integrated simple to use shipping solition.  Shipzi benefits the small business owner by being a free to use multi-carrier shipping solution that seamlessly integrates with their eCommerce software and makes shipping easier & faster. Millions of small and medium size businesses use eCommerce marketplaces and web platforms like Etsy, eBay, Magento, Volusion to sell their goods and services. Shipzi has spent over a year building the technology to deliver web based shipping management functionality from the cloud. We’re attacking a $6-billion a year home based and SMB online shipping market. We’re providing functionality that stamps.com, UPS, DHL, & USPS can’t.  In a fast growing market with over 30 million online home based and SMB businesses selling products using eCommerce platforms, Shipzi is positioned to become the standard shipping platform. Description: Local Government Information Systems (LOGIS) is a consortium of Minnesota local government units.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Minneapolis-Saint Paul Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Headquartered in Golden Valley, Local Government Information Systems (LOGIS) is a Joint Powers, intergovernmental consortium of Minnesota local government units. The mission of LOGIS is to “Facilitate leading-edge, effective and adaptable public sector technology solutions through the sharing of ideas, risks and resources in a member-driven consortium.” The LOGIS consortium is controlled by its members. LOGIS’ Board of Directors is composed of one representative from each agency. All funding decisions are controlled by the members through an annual budget, an annual work plan, and by action of an Executive Committee, acting as officers of the Board. This committee meets quarterly and establishes operating policies, sets service charges, and approves expenditures. LOGIS was founded in 1972 by seven cities – Golden Valley, Crystal, Eden Prairie, Edina, St. Louis Park, Coon Rapids and Brooklyn Center – that were looking to pool resources and save taxpayer dollars. LOGIS currently has 73 member organizations and serves more than 2.1 million residents throughout Minnesota.
